    {
      "id": "2612a17ac961dfd9aa580ce5b0300bc2385763b1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 257,
        "name": "Keith Mannthey",
        "email": "keith.mannthey@intel.com",
        "username": "kmannth",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-18 21:14:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nJohn,  we are getting some pretty ugly mds panics while unmounting the mds.  It is not clear you patch is the cause but it for sure brings it out. \n\nThere is an LU tracking the isse http://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2648",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "d69beb9e15e8cb46f3e3d9476c976513a770c532",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-18 22:40:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThanks for the heads up. Am reviewing now.\n\nmdt_procfs_fini() looks pretty sketchy, I may be uncovering some latent badness.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "45832fac40dfbac1e5204bf04efa718b63cabf43",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-24 21:55:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Abandoned\n\nThe memory corruption was due to the change in mdt_export_stats_init(). I should have used LPROC_MDT_LAST + #obd_ops instead of LPROC_MDT_LAST. Note that master is also incorrect here since it uses #md_ops + LPROC_MDT_LAST. After review I think a more systematic removal of obd_ops counters from the per-client stats is the best approach.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    }
  ],
